Greetings!

 

We are pleased to present the “Communiqué from DNA” for the month of March, which brings you various initiatives and news from our Learning Journey and much more.

 

Highlights of March 2020:

 

  • March Learning Calendar showcased the following programs:
    • Communicate to Conquer – 3rd March 2020
      • Coverage: Communication, Understanding Others- Emotional Intelligence, Ladder of Inference, Circle of Influence, Building and Maintaining Relationships
      • Number of Participants - 6
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator - Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 50%

 

    • EXPLORE – Session 4 – 3rd March 2020
      • Coverage:  Situational Leadership II
      • Number of Participants - 11
      • Duration - 8 hours
      • Facilitator – Sujatha Das
      • e-NPS – 85%

 

    • EXPLORE – Session 5 – 9th March 2020
      • Coverage:  Practicum and Leader Connect (Sridhar Garla)
      • Number of Participants - 11
      • Duration - 8 hours
      • Facilitator – Sujatha Das / Sridhar Garla
      • e-NPS – 100%

 

    • Delivering Effective Learning – 19th, 20th, 26th and 27th March 2020
      • Coverage:  Definitions, Nine Principles of Learning, Learning Styles, Needs Analysis, Modes of Instruction, Evaluation and Effectiveness, Tips and Tricks, Training Aids, Path of a Learner, Practice makes perfect!
      • Number of Participants - 11
      • Duration - 16 hours
      • Facilitator - Sujatha Das
      • e-NPS – 89%

 

    • Bridge Barriers – 26th March 2020
      • Coverage:  Resolving Conflicts, Listening Skills and Barriers, Adapting to Cultural differences
      • Number of Participants - 12
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator – Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS - 100%
    • I-LEAD – 10th March / 16th March
      • Coverage: Operational Efficiency for Managers
      • Number of Participants - 24 
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator – Multiple
      • e-NPS – 60%

 

    • Present Like a Pro – 17th / 18th March 2020
      • Coverage:  Barriers to Effective Presentation, 3 Steps to Presenting- Planning, Organizing, Delivering, Analyzing the Audience, Brainstorming and Mind Mapping, Visual Aids and Signposting, 3 Vs of Presenting, Handling Questions, Controlling Nerves while presenting, Top Tips for Effective Presentation
      • Number of Participants - 19
      • Duration - 8 hours
      • Facilitator – Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 64%

 

    • Together Everyone Achieves More – 19th March 2020
      • Coverage: Characteristics of a Good Team, Traits of a Good Team Player, Communication, Effective Teamwork
      • Number of Participants - 11
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator – Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 64%

 

    • Making Time Count – 23rd / 24th March
      • Coverage:  Managing Time – Pareto Analysis, Time Management Mistakes, Time Orientation, Planning, PAST Method, Task Planning, Goal Setting, Prioritization, Tips for Improving Your Concentration, Dealing with Distractions
      • Number of Participants - 14
      • Duration - 8 hours
      • Facilitator – Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 88%

 

    • Culture of Service – 27th March 2020
      • Coverage: What is Customer Centricity, Moment of Truth, Ways How to Be More Customer-Centric, Perception Vs. Reality, Listening, Empathy and Ownership, Service ‘NO’, Handling Difficult Situations, Communicating Bad News, Telephone Etiquette
      • Number of Participants - 9
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator - Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 100% 
  •  
    • BELBIN – 30th March 2020
      • Coverage:  Introduction to BELBIN, Understand Preferred team role, How to build productive working relationships, Self-awareness and personal effectiveness, Building mutual trust and understanding
      • Number of Participants - 8
      • Duration - 4 hours
      • Facilitator - Shaira Banu
      • e-NPS – 100%

 

  • Knowledge Sharing Sessions by Practice Groups:
    • Web-Based Crawling Images – Facilitated by Janjanan Sudheer
    • Named Entity Recognition – Facilitated by Riddi Dasgupta
    • Visualization of Power BI, R & Python – Facilitated by Rajesh Patil
    • Stochastic Models in Finance – Tushar Prakash Patil
